To select Dynamic Wallpapers, you may need to take a few steps
If a custom Dynamic Wallpaper only shows the dark version of the wallpaper:

    potential solution 1: workaround for auto-dark selection (recommended)
    
        1. don't set the custom wallpaper in Desktop settings
        2. set the wallpaper to a default Dynamic Wallpaper -- like the Montery graphic
        3. set the wallpaper to "Light" then "Dynamic"
        4. close the Desktop settings
        5. set the new wallpaper by right-clicking on an image in Finder and selecting "Set Desktop Picture"
    
    potential soution 3: navigate the unselectable menu with tab (not recommended)
    
        1. open Keyboard settings and go to the Shortcuts submenu
        2. tick "use keyboard navigation to move focus between controls"
        3. go back to the Desktop settings
        4. select the desired wallpaper
        5. press tab until you reach the Dynamic Wallpaper dropdown
        6. select Dynamic
    
    potential solution 2: move files to "/System/Library/Desktop Pictures" (untested, not recommended)
        
        1. in a terminal, execute 'open "/System/Library/Desktop Pictures"'
        2. copy over desired wallpapers to "/System/Library/Desktop Pictures" [MUST DISABLE SIP - ONLY DO THIS IF YOU ARE POSITIVE YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS]
        3. select them from the Apple Wallpapers section in the wallpaper settings
    
    potential solution 3: move files to "/Library/Desktop Pictures" (untested, not recommended)
    
        1. create a new folder "/Library/Desktop Pictures" if it does not exist
        2. copy over desired wallpapers to "/Library/Desktop Pictures"
        3. select them from the Apple Wallpapers section in the wallpaper settings
        
To create Dynamic Wallpapers:

    Option 1: Dynamic Wallpaper Club (recommended)
    
        https://dynamicwallpaper.club/create

    option 2: wallpapper (not recommended, time and sun methods are both impossible to get right)
    
        https://github.com/mczachurski/wallpapper
        https://itnext.io/macos-mojave-dynamic-wallpaper-fd26b0698223
        
        function walp(){
            wallpapper -i "$1".json -o "$1".heic && wallpapper -e "$1".heic
        }
        
    Option 3: 24 Hour Wallpaper (completely untested and $10)
    
        https://apps.apple.com/us/app/24-hour-wallpaper/id1226087575?ls=1&mt=12
    
    Tools:
    
        elevation and azimuth calculator: https://keisan.casio.com/exec/system/1224682277
        dynamic wallpaper seperator: https://strukturag.github.io/libheif/
        wallpapers location: https://nono.ma/location-of-apple-desktop-pictures-big-sur
    
    
